{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/people/boris-johnson","content_id":"ec7cb2ba-3c02-48c5-a918-1f4a211499ae","description":"Boris Johnson was Prime Minister from 24 July 2019 to 6 September 2022. He was previously Foreign Secretary from 13 July 2016 to 9 July 2018. He was Conservative MP for Uxbridge and South Ruislip from May 2015 to June 2023. Previously he was the MP for Henley from June 2001 to June 2008.","details":{"body":"<p>Boris Johnson was Prime Minister from 24 July 2019 to 6 September 2022. He was previously Foreign Secretary from 13 July 2016 to 9 July 2018.</p>\n\n<p>He was Conservative MP for Uxbridge and South Ruislip from May 2015 to June 2023. Previously he was the MP for Henley from June 2001 to June 2008.</p>\n","full_name":"Boris Johnson","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Boris Johnson","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/614b350bd3bf7f718518026a/s465_Boris_Johnson_.jpg"},"privy_counsellor":true},"document_type":"person","first_published_at":"2016-07-13T20:15:12+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/boris-johnson","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/boris-johnson","base_path":"/government/people/boris-johnson","content_id":"ec7cb2ba-3c02-48c5-a918-1f4a211499ae","document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-11-27T17:29:25Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Boris Johnson","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/boris-johnson","withdrawn":false}],"role_appointments":[{"content_id":"4fd5a00d-8a80-4fa9-ac0e-c5305808f56a","details":{"current":false,"ended_on":"2022-09-06T00:00:00+01:00","person_appointment_order":5575,"started_on":"2019-07-24T00:00:00+01:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"person":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/boris-johnson","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/boris-johnson","base_path":"/government/people/boris-johnson","content_id":"ec7cb2ba-3c02-48c5-a918-1f4a211499ae","details":{"body":"<p>Boris Johnson was Prime Minister from 24 July 2019 to 6 September 2022. He was previously Foreign Secretary from 13 July 2016 to 9 July 2018.</p>\n\n<p>He was Conservative MP for Uxbridge and South Ruislip from May 2015 to June 2023. Previously he was the MP for Henley from June 2001 to June 2008.</p>\n","image":{"alt_text":"The Rt Hon Boris Johnson","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/614b350bd3bf7f718518026a/s465_Boris_Johnson_.jpg"}},"document_type":"person","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2023-11-27T17:29:25Z","schema_name":"person","title":"The Rt Hon Boris Johnson","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/boris-johnson","withdrawn":false}],"role":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/ministers/minister-for-the-civil-service","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/ministers/minister-for-the-civil-service","base_path":"/government/ministers/minister-for-the-civil-service","content_id":"846a7351-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Minister for the Civil Service is responsible for regulating the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.civilservice.gov.uk/\">Civil Service</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1992/61/contents\">Civil Service (Management Functions) Act of 1992</a>, allows the Minister for the Civil Service to delegate power to other ministers and devolved administrations.</p>\n\n<p>This role was created in 1968 and is always held by the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/ministers/prime-minister\">Prime Minister</a>.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null,"seniority":3,"whip_organisation":{}},"document_type":"ministerial_role","links":{"ordered_parent_organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"D2","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/cabinet-office","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/cabinet-office","base_path":"/government/organisat